cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper deals with image manipulation and computer vision tasks, specifically modeling daytime changes in high resolution photographs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves generative models and image-to-image translation, which falls under the sub-category cs.GR (Graphics). The new upsampling scheme used in the model can be considered a machine learning technique, which could place the paper under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves training a model without domain labels, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the results of the model are evaluated using both GAN metrics and human evaluation, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
